text: Tia Carrere (born January 2, 1967) is an American movie and television performer. Her career was launched around 1985. She was born in Honolulu, Hawaii to Filipino parents. Her notable movies include the 1992 comedy Wayne's World, and Disney's 2001 animated feature film Lilo and Stitch. She began her career with the TV series Airwolf. Other television shows and movies followed. In 2006, she was a contestant on the show Dancing with the Stars.
